rification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_models.py::TestMetadataOptions::test_from_options -v`\n179: \n180: ### Phase 5: Integration Tests (ST-5)\n181: \n182: - [ ] **T5.1**: Verify PackRuntime uses MetadataService.load_metadata\n183:   - Purpose: Ensure PackRuntime correctly loads metadata via MetadataService\n184:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n185:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_pack_loads_metadata -v`\n186: \n187: - [ ] **T5.2**: Verify PackRuntime uses MetadataService.save_metadata\n188:   - Purpose: Ensure PackRuntime correctly saves metadata via MetadataService\n189:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py`\n190:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_pack_saves_metadata -v`\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T5.3**: Verify BuildRuntime updates version in metadata\n193:   - Purpose: Ensure BuildRuntime increments version field in metadata\n194:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py`\n195:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::test_build_updates_version -v`\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T5.4**: Verify PublishRuntime updates k8s_deployment info\n198:   - Purpose: Ensure PublishRuntime updates k8s_deployment field in metadata\n199:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py`\n200:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::test_publish_updates_deployment_info -v`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T5.5**: Verify InvokeRuntime reads agent_endpoint from metadata\n203:   - Purpose: Ensure InvokeRuntime reads agent_endpoint field for invocation\n204:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py`\n205:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py::test_invoke_reads_endpoint -v`\n206: \n207: - [ ] **T5.6**: Verify StatusRuntime loads metadata for status check\n208:   - Purpose: Ensure StatusRuntime loads metadata to check agent status\n209:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py`\n210:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py::test_status_reads_metadata -v`\n211: \n212: - [ ] **T5.7**: Verify MetadataService exported from services package\n213:   - Purpose: Ensure MetadataService is importable from services package\n214:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py`\n215:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services import MetadataService, AgentMetadata; print('OK')\"`\n216: \n217: - [ ] **T5.8**: Verify MetadataOptions exported from models package\n218:   - Purpose: Ensure MetadataOptions is importable from models package\n219:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/__init__.py`\n220:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.models import MetadataOptions; print('OK')\"`\n221: \n222: ---\n223: \n224: ## Task Dependencies\n225: \n226: ```\n227: T1.1 (AgentMetadata model) ──┬── T1.2 (language validator)\n228:                              ├── T1.3 (build_mode validator)\n229:                              └── T1.4 (port validator)\n230: \n231: T1.1-T1.4 ──────────────────┬── T2.1 (MetadataOptions dataclass)\n232:                             └── T2.2 (from_options method)\n233: \n234: T2.1 ───────────────────────┬── T3.1 (MetadataService init)\n235:                             ├── T3.2 (load_metadata)\n236:                             ├── T3.3 (save_metadata)\n237:                             └── T3.4 (update_metadata)\n238: \n239: T3.2 + T3.3 ────────────────┬── T3.4 (update_metadata)\n240:                             ├── T3.5 (validate_workspace)\n241:                             ├── T3.6 (_validate_python_workspace)\n242:                             └── T3.7 (_validate_java_workspace)\n243: \n244: T3.5 ───────────────────────┬── T3.6 (_validate_python_workspace)\n245:                             └── T3.7 (_validate_java_workspace)\n246: \n247: T1.1-T3.7 ──────────────────┬── T4.1-T4.18 (comprehensive unit tests)\n248:                             └── T5.1-T5.8 (integration tests)\n249: \n250: T4.1-T4.18 ──────────────────┬── T5.1-T5.8 (integration tests)\n251: ```\n252: \n253: ---\n254: \n255: ## Verification Commands\n256: \n257: | Task | Verification Command |\n258: |------|----------------------|\n259: | T1.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_valid -v` |\n260: | T1.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_language -v` |\n261: | T1.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_build_mode -v` |\n262: | T1.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_port_low -v` |\n263: | T2.1 | `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; print('OK')\" |\n264: | T2.2 | `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; opt = MetadataOptions.from_options({'agent_name': 'test'}); print(opt.agent_name)\"` |\n265: | T3.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_load_agent_metadata_yaml -v` |\n266: | T3.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_load_fallback_agent_yaml -v` |\n267: | T3.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_save_excludes_none -v` |\n268: | T3.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_update -v` |\n269: | T3.5 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_validate_workspace_python -v` |\n270: | T3.6 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_validate_python_workspace_has_py -v` |\n271: | T3.7 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_validate_java_workspace_has_pom -v` |\n272: | T4.1-T4.18 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py -v` |\n273: | T5.1 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_pack_loads_metadata -v` |\n274: | T5.2 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py::test_pack_saves_metadata -v` |\n275: | T5.3 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py::test_build_updates_version -v` |\n276: | T5.4 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py::test_publish_updates_deployment_info -v` |\n277: | T5.5 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py::test_invoke_reads_endpoint -v` |\n278: | T5.6 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py::test_status_reads_metadata -v` |\n279: | T5.7 | `python -c \"from agentcube.services import MetadataService, AgentMetadata; print('OK')\" |\n280: | T5.8 | `python -c \"from agentcube.models import MetadataOptions; print('OK')\" |\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## Acceptance Criteria\n285: \n286: - [x] `AgentMetadata` Pydantic BaseModel defined with all 20+ fields from design\n287: - [x] `language` validator accepts 'python' and 'java' (lowercase normalized)\n288: - [x] `build_mode` validator accepts 'local' and 'cloud' (lowercase normalized)\n289: - [x] `port` validator accepts values in range 1-65535\n290: - [x] `MetadataOptions` dataclass defined with all CLI options fields\n291: - [x] `MetadataOptions.from_options()` factory filters None values from dict\n292: - [x] `MetadataService.__init__` stores verbose flag\n293: - [x] `load_metadata()` falls back through filename list ['agent_metadata.yaml', 'agent.yaml', 'metadata.yaml']\n294: - [x] `load_metadata()` raises FileNotFoundError when no metadata files exist\n295: - [x] `load_metadata()` raises ValueError on malformed YAML\n296: - [x] `load_metadata()` raises ValueError on schema validation failure\n297: - [x] `save_metadata()` saves to agent_metadata.yaml\n298: - [x] `save_metadata()` uses yaml.dump with default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False\n299: - [x] `save_metadata()` excludes None values with model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n300: - [ ] `update_metadata()` loads, applies updates dict, saves, and returns new AgentMetadata\n301: - [ ] `validate_workspace()` returns True for valid workspace\n302: - [ ] `validate_workspace()` raises ValueError for invalid workspace\n303: - [ ] `_validate_python_workspace()` checks for at least one *.py file\n304: - [ ] `_validate_java_workspace()` checks for pom.xml\n305: - [ ] All 18 unit tests pass for MetadataService and models\n306: - [ ] All 8 integration tests pass with runtime classes\n307: - [ ] MetadataService and AgentMetadata exported from services package\n308: - [ ] MetadataOptions exported from models package\n309: \n310: ---\n311: \n312: ## File Changes Summary\n313: \n314: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n315: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n316: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Modify | 79→~120 | Add update_metadata, validate_workspace, and validation helpers |\n317: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Done | 26 | MetadataOptions dataclass implementation complete |\n318: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py` | Modify | 161→~250 | Add tests for update, validate, and comprehensive validation |\n319: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_models.py` | Create | ~30 | MetadataOptions unit tests |\n320: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Modify | - | Export MetadataService, AgentMetadata |\n321: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/__init__.py` | Modify | - | Export MetadataOptions |\n322: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_pack_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Integration: PackRuntime uses MetadataService |\n323: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_build_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Integration: BuildRuntime updates metadata |\n324: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Integration: PublishRuntime updates metadata |\n325: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Integration: InvokeRuntime reads metadata |\n326: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py` | Uses | - | Integration: StatusRuntime loads metadata |\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ## Implementation Notes\n331: \n332: ### Metadata File Fallback Priority\n333: \n334: The `load_metadata()` method searches for metadata files in this order:\n335: 1. `agent_metadata.yaml` (canonical, preferred)\n336: 2. `agent.yaml` (fallback)\n337: 3. `metadata.yaml` (fallback)\n338: \n339: This allows backward compatibility with existing agent projects.\n340: \n341: ### YAML Serialization Configuration\n342: \n343: ```python\n344: yaml.dump(\n345:     metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n346:     f,\n347:     default_flow_style=False,  # Use block style, not flow style\n348:     indent=2,                   # 2-space indentation\n349:     sort_keys=False,            # Preserve field order from model\n350: )\n351: ```\n352: \n353: ### Language-Specific Workspace Validation\n354: \n355: | Language | Validation Requirement |\n356: |----------|----------------------|\n357: | python | At least one `*.py` file in workspace root |\n358: | java | `pom.xml` file must exist in workspace |\n359: \n360: ### Error Handling Patterns\n361: \n362: ```python\n363: try:\n364:     with open(filepath, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n365:         data = yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n366:     return AgentMetadata(**data)\n367: except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n368:     raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML in {filename}: {e}\")\n369: except ValidationError as e:\n370:     raise ValueError(f\"Schema validation failed: {e}\")\n371: ```\n372: \n373: ### Constants Reference\n374: \n375: ```python\n376: METADATA_FILENAMES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n377: CANONICAL_METADATA_FILENAME = \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n378: SUPPORTED_LANGUAGES = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n379: SUPPORTED_BUILD_MODES = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n380: DEFAULT_PORT = 8080\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## Implementation Timeline\n386: \n387: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n388: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n389: | Phase 1: AgentMetadata Model | T1.1-T1.4 | Done | 100% |\n390: | Phase 2: MetadataOptions | T2.1-T2.2 | Done | 100% |\n391: | Phase 3: MetadataService Core | T3.1-T3.3 | Done | 100% |\n392: | Phase 3: MetadataService Core | T3.4-T3.7 | Pending | 0% |\n393: | Phase 4: Comprehensive Tests | T4.1-T4.10 | Done | 100% |\n394: | Phase 4: Comprehensive Tests | T4.11-T4.18 | Pending | 0% |\n395: | Phase 5: Integration Tests | T5.1-T5.8 | Pending | 0% |\n396: \n397: **Total Progress: 46% Complete (13/28 tasks)**\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ## References\n402: \n403: - Design: `changes/AR-025/design.md`\n404: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n405: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (workspace validation, metadata format)\n406: - AR-024 — DockerService pattern (similar task structure)\n\n(End of file - total 406 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: AgentMetadata Model (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Implement `AgentMetadata` Pydantic BaseModel with all required fields\n  - Purpose: Define primary data model for agent configuration stored as YAML","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775877184440,"end":1775877184466}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877184471,"sessionID":"ses_28578efe2ffeHdJlje1Uvxen4e","part":{"id":"prt_d7a875026001te7s5GPd5KRfVI","messageID":"msg_d7a873990001yjlgYS9SoL04Aq","sessionID":"ses_28578efe2ffeHdJlje1Uvxen4e","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e2662dfd4ac74f758dbb83bb67acd137","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: This AR implements the `MetadataService` and associated data models (`AgentMetadata` and `MetadataOptions`) that manage agent configuration throughout the CLI lifecycle. The service handles loading, saving, and validating YAML metadata files that persist agent state across `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, and `status` operations.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ```\n20: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n21: │                         CLI Commands                                 │\n22: │  pack │ build │ publish │ invoke │ status                           │\n23: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n24:                       │\n25:                       ▼\n26: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n27: │                      Runtime Classes                                 │\n28: │  PackRuntime │ BuildRuntime │ PublishRuntime │ InvokeRuntime │      │\n29: │  StatusRuntime                                                       │\n30: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n31:                       │\n32:                       ▼\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │                      MetadataService                                 │\n35: │  - load_metadata(workspace_path) → AgentMetadata                    │\n36: │  - save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata) → None                   │\n37: │  - update_metadata(workspace_path, updates) → AgentMetadata         │\n38: │  - validate_workspace(workspace_path) → bool                        │\n39: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n40:                       │\n41:                       ▼\n42: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n43: │                      Data Models                                     │\n44: │  AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel) ← YAML serialization            │\n45: │  MetadataOptions (dataclass) ← CLI options mapping                  │\n46: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n47:                       │\n48:                       ▼\n49: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n50: │                      Storage                                         │\n51: │  {workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml (canonical)                        │\n52: │  {workspace}/agent.yaml (fallback)                                  │\n53: │  {workspace}/metadata.yaml (fallback)                               │\n54: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n55: ```\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## Data Structures\n60: \n61: ### AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n62: \n63: Primary data model for agent configuration, stored as YAML.\n64: \n65: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n66: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n67: | `agent_name` | `str` | **required** | Unique name identifying the agent |\n68: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n69: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n70: | `entrypoint` | `str` | **required** | Command to launch the agent |\n71: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n72: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n73: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n74: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n75: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n76: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n77: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n78: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n79: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n80: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n81: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n82: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n83: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n84: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n85: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n86: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n87: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n88: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n89: \n90: #### Validators\n91: \n92: ```python\n93: @field_validator('language')\n94: @classmethod\n95: def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n96:     v = v.lower()\n97:     if v not in ['python', 'java']:\n98:         raise ValueError(f'language must be one of: python, java')\n99:     return v\n100: \n101: @field_validator('build_mode')\n102: @classmethod\n103: def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n104:     v = v.lower()\n105:     if v not in ['local', 'cloud']:\n106:         raise ValueError(f'build_mode must be one of: local, cloud')\n107:     return v\n108: \n109: @field_validator('port')\n110: @classmethod\n111: def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n112:     if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n113:         raise ValueError('port must be between 1 and 65535')\n114:     return v\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### MetadataOptions (dataclass)\n120: \n121: CLI options dataclass for mapping command-line arguments to metadata fields.\n122: \n123: | Field | Type | Default |\n124: |-------|------|---------|\n125: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n126: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n127: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n128: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n129: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n130: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n131: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n132: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n133: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n134: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n135: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n136: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n137: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n138: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n139: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n140: \n141: ```python\n142: @dataclass\n143: class MetadataOptions:\n144:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n145:     language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n146:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n147:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n148:     build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n149:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n150:     description: Optional[str] = None\n151:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n152:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n153:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n154:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n155:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n156:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n157:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n158:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n159: \n160:     @classmethod\n161:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n162:         return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if v is not None})\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## API Contracts\n168: \n169: ### MetadataService\n170: \n171: ```python\n172: class MetadataService:\n173:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n174:         self.verbose = verbose\n175:         self._metadata_filenames = [\n176:             \"agent_metadata.yaml\",\n177:             \"agent.yaml\",\n178:             \"metadata.yaml\",\n179:         ]\n180: \n181:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n182:         \"\"\"\n183:         Load metadata from workspace, falling back through filename list.\n184:         \n185:         Raises:\n186:             FileNotFoundError: If no metadata file exists\n187:             ValueError: If YAML content violates AgentMetadata schema\n188:         \"\"\"\n189: \n190:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n191:         \"\"\"\n192:         Save metadata to {workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml using yaml.dump.\n193:         \n194:         Settings:\n195:             - default_flow_style=False\n196:             - indent=2\n197:             - sort_keys=False\n198:             - model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n199:         \"\"\"\n200: \n201:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n202:         \"\"\"\n203:         Load, apply updates, save, and return new AgentMetadata.\n204:         \"\"\"\n205: \n206:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n207:         \"\"\"\n208:         Validate workspace structure and language-specific requirements.\n209:         \n210:         Returns:\n211:             True if valid\n212:             \n213:         Raises:\n214:             ValueError: If workspace invalid\n215:         \"\"\"\n216: \n217:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n218:         \"\"\"\n219:         Check for at least one *.py file in workspace root.\n220:         \n221:         Raises:\n222:             ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n223:         \"\"\"\n224: \n225:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n226:         \"\"\"\n227:         Check for pom.xml in workspace.\n228:         \n229:         Raises:\n230:             ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")\n231:         \"\"\"\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ### Metadata File Format\n237: \n238: ```yaml\n239: agent_name: my-agent\n240: description: A sample agent\n241: language: python\n242: entrypoint: python main.py\n243: port: 8080\n244: build_mode: local\n245: version: v1.0.0\n246: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n247: registry_url: \"\"\n248: registry_username: \"\"\n249: registry_password: \"\"\n250: agent_endpoint: null\n251: workload_manager_url: null\n252: router_url: null\n253: readiness_probe_path: null\n254: readiness_probe_port: null\n255: agent_id: null\n256: session_id: null\n257: image:\n258:   name: my-agent\n259:   tag: latest\n260:   id: sha256:...\n261:   size: 150MB\n262:   build_time: 45s\n263: auth:\n264:   type: bearer\n265: k8s_deployment:\n266:   type: AgentRuntime\n267:   namespace: default\n268:   deployment_name: my-agent\n269:   service_name: my-agent-service\n270:   node_port: 30001\n271: ```\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ## Error Handling\n276: \n277: ### Exception Types\n278: \n279: | Exception | Scenario |\n280: |-----------|----------|\n281: | `FileNotFoundError` | Workspace or metadata file not found |\n282: | `ValueError` | Schema validation failure, missing required field |\n283: | `pydantic.ValidationError` | Pydantic field validation failure |\n284: \n285: ### Error Handling Patterns\n286: \n287: ```python\n288: def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n289:     for filename in self._metadata_filenames:\n290:         path = workspace_path / filename\n291:         if path.exists():\n292:             try:\n293:                 with open(path, 'r') as f:\n294:                     data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n295:                 return AgentMetadata(**data)\n296:             except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n297:                 raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML in {filename}: {e}\")\n298:             except ValidationError as e:\n299:                 raise ValueError(f\"Schema validation failed: {e}\")\n300:     \n301:     raise FileNotFoundError(\n302:         f\"No metadata file found in {workspace_path}. \"\n303:         f\"Expected one of: {', '.join(self._metadata_filenames)}\"\n304:     )\n305: ```\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## Testing Strategy\n310: \n311: ### Unit Tests\n312: \n313: | Test Case | Description |\n314: |-----------|-------------|\n315: | `test_load_metadata_primary` | Load from `agent_metadata.yaml` |\n316: | `test_load_metadata_fallback_agent_yaml` | Fallback to `agent.yaml` |\n317: | `test_load_metadata_fallback_metadata_yaml` | Fallback to `metadata.yaml` |\n318: | `test_load_metadata_not_found` | Raise `FileNotFoundError` when all missing |\n319: | `test_load_metadata_invalid_yaml` | Raise `ValueError` on malformed YAML |\n320: | `test_load_metadata_schema_validation` | Raise `ValueError` on Pydantic validation failure |\n321: | `test_save_metadata_excludes_none` | Verify `exclude_none=True` behavior |\n322: | `test_save_metadata_yaml_format` | Verify YAML formatting (indent, no flow style) |\n323: | `test_update_metadata_partial` | Update specific fields only |\n324: | `test_validate_python_workspace` | Check for `*.py` files |\n325: | `test_validate_java_workspace` | Check for `pom.xml` |\n326: | `test_validate_language_python` | Validate `language='python'` |\n327: | `test_validate_language_java` | Validate `language='java'` |\n328: | `test_validate_language_invalid` | Reject invalid language |\n329: | `test_validate_build_mode_local` | Validate `build_mode='local'` |\n330: | `test_validate_build_mode_cloud` | Validate `build_mode='cloud'` |\n331: | `test_validate_port_range` | Validate port 1-65535 |\n332: | `test_validate_port_out_of_range` | Reject port outside range |\n333: | `test_metadata_options_from_options` | Create MetadataOptions from dict |\n334: \n335: ### Integration Tests\n336: \n337: | Test Case | Description |\n338: |-----------|-------------|\n339: | `test_pack_loads_metadata` | PackRuntime uses MetadataService.load_metadata |\n340: | `test_pack_saves_metadata` | PackRuntime uses MetadataService.save_metadata |\n341: | `test_build_updates_version` | BuildRuntime increments version in metadata |\n342: | `test_publish_updates_deployment_info` | PublishRuntime updates `k8s_deployment` |\n343: | `test_invoke_reads_endpoint` | InvokeRuntime reads `agent_endpoint` from metadata |\n344: | `test_status_reads_metadata` | StatusRuntime loads metadata for status check |\n345: \n346: ---\n347: \n348: ## File Structure\n349: \n350: ```\n351: cmd/cli/\n352: ├── agentcube/\n353: │   ├── models/\n354: │   │   ├── __init__.py              # Module marker\n355: │   │   └── pack_models.py           # MetadataOptions dataclass\n356: │   ├── services/\n357: │   │   ├── __init__.py              # Services package docstring\n358: │   │   └── metadata_service.py      # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n359: │   ├── runtime/\n360: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py          # Uses MetadataService\n361: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py         # Uses MetadataService\n362: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py       # Uses MetadataService\n363: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py        # Uses MetadataService\n364: │   │   └── status_runtime.py        # Uses MetadataService\n365: │   └── ...\n366: └── tests/\n367:     ├── test_metadata_service.py     # MetadataService unit tests\n368:     ├── test_agent_metadata.py       # AgentMetadata model tests\n369:     ├── test_pack_models.py          # MetadataOptions tests\n370:     └── integration/\n371:         └── test_metadata_flow.py    # Integration tests\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ## Dependencies\n377: \n378: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n379: |---------|---------|---------|\n380: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | BaseModel, validators, serialization |\n381: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | YAML load/dump |\n382: | `pathlib` | stdlib | Path handling |\n383: \n384: ---\n385: \n386: ## Implementation Notes\n387: \n388: ### Constants\n389: \n390: ```python\n391: METADATA_FILENAMES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n392: CANONICAL_METADATA_FILENAME = \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n393: SUPPORTED_LANGUAGES = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n394: SUPPORTED_BUILD_MODES = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n395: DEFAULT_PORT = 8080\n396: ```\n397: \n398: ### YAML Serialization\n399: \n400: ```python\n401: yaml.dump(\n402:     metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n403:     default_flow_style=False,\n404:     indent=2,\n405:     sort_keys=False,\n406: )\n407: ```\n408: \n409: ### Language Validation\n410: \n411: Lowercase normalization before validation:\n412: ```python\n413: language = options.get('language', 'python').lower()\n414: ```\n415: \n416: ---\n417: \n418: ## References\n419: \n420: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n421: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (workspace validation, metadata format)\n\n(End of file - total 421 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThis AR implements the `MetadataService` and associated data models (`AgentMetadata` and `MetadataOptions`) that manage agent configuration throughout the CLI lifecycle. The service handles loading, saving, and validating YAML metadata files that persist agent state across `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, and `status` operations.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/design.md","time":{"start":1775877184435,"end":1775877184469}}}}
